node.text:
Happy Valentines Day! We have a challenge for you. It’s all explained in the video above, or you can just keep reading below!

If you decide to participate, tag us in your post or story so we can repost our favorites and spread the love :) Bringing Kara coffee in bed every morning guarantees that no matter what happens the rest of the day, I have at least done one nice thing for her! It’s one of the best things I do for our relationship, and we love it when other people tag us bringing their partner coffee too, because we want this little habit to become a part of as many relationships as possible! 
So, on this Valentines day, we’re issuing you an official challenge to bring your partner coffee (or their drink of choice) in bed everyday for the rest of the month!

If for some reason your circumstances don’t allow you to bring your loved one coffee in bed, your challenge is to come up with some way you can add one thoughtful thing into your daily routine.

That’s it. There’s no prize or anything for completing the challenge. I just wanted to spread the idea of intentionally doing something thoughtful for your partner everyday.

node.text:
How did we end up on a solar powered yacht in Mallorca?! It’s actually a pretty funny story…➡️

March 2020: Pandemic was still new and scary. We were quarantined in a hotel in Singapore with so many unknowns.

How were we going to keep our channel going during a pandemic? Is this the end of travel for a month? The summer? a YEAR maybe? 😱

We starting looking at our options. One of our crazy ideas was to live on a boat 🧐

This sent Nate down a major internet rabbit hole where he eventually stumbled upon @silent_yachts_headquarters - one of a kind, 100% solar powered yachts. Our minds were BLOWN. 

Nate fired off an email to see if they’d be interested in letting us take one of their boats around the world. “Why not? How hard can it be” am I right?

To our surprise they responded, but clearly we did not follow through with this idea 😂 However it did spark an online relationship with the team at Silent Yachts. And we’d be lying if we didn’t say we have dreamed of boarding one of these yachts everyday since!

Fast forward to last week: Silent Yachts saw that we were in Italy, and they just happened to have a few available nights on one of their yachts here in Mallorca. And BOOM here we are! 

The morals of this story are 1. It never hurts to ask and 2. this is why we never book our travel in advance! 😉

node.text: WE GOT ON AN AIRPLANE AND FLEW TO ANOTHER COUNTRY AND MADE A VIDEO ABOUT IT AND PUT IT ON OUR YOUTUBE CHANNEL. THAT IS ALL 💃🏻 Actually there’s more….We packed a suitcase. Went to a lounge. Flew over the ocean. Ate mediocre airplane food. Cheers’ed to our wedding anniversary with yummy champagne. Watched movies instead of sleeping. Walked around Rome in a beautiful jet-lagged daze. Cried over carbonara. That’s actually all. My heart (and belly) are full.

node.text:
It feels surreal to be back in our favorite place in the world 😭❤️🙌🏻

On our travel day to Italy, we received lots of questions about travel restrictions in Europe. Every country is different, and it seems like the rules are always changing, so it can be a little overwhelming. 

If you’re planning a trip to Europe this summer @omio is a great resource for must-have travel information!

Their Open Travel Index allows you to enter where you are traveling to/from, and it gives you all the details about how to get there safely and what to expect! Plus they will notify you about any updates leading up to your departure ✈️

Swipe up on our stories today to check them out before booking your travel 🌎

There are a lot of days when Nate and I just look at each other and say, “Our life is nuts.” This was one of those days 🥜 

Our new mid-week video is waiting for you on YouTube 🤗 

Having *zero* interest in sports of any kind, the #Indy500 was an experience I had no idea I would enjoy SO much! First we rode 200 mph with THE 81 year old @andrettimario, and then got to be in the pit when @heliocastroneves crossed the finish line and won the race. I don’t think the energy we felt on this day will ever be matched! 🏁

Still cannot believe we got to play around in @heliocastroneves pit and use the crazy air gun tire changing thingy!!! 

Before we went to the #Indy500 last weekend, I knew nothing about racing (and still kinda don’t…) BUT now we have a whole new appreciation for this sport! 🏁 

Go watch today’s vlog to get the full behind the scenes tour of the @indianapolismotorspeedway over on YouTube! ❤️

node.text:
Full transparency: Last week I couldn’t have even told you what the Indy 500 was. This week, we are standing on the finish line of the largest sporting arena in the world - and STARSTRUCK IS AN UNDERSTATEMENT 🤩

That’s one of my favorite things about our life. After a few documentaries (which pretty much made me an expert😉), I have a whole new appreciation for this sport and the insanely talented athletes here today! We got to meet the legendary @heliocastroneves🕺🏻tour his RV, and had full behind the scenes access to the Indianapolis Motor Speedway. WHAT A DAY 🤯 and this is only the beginning! 

PS this is all because of you. We asked here on Instagram if any of you had any connections to the Indy 500 because that’s what everyone told us we must do in this state, and you made it happen! 🙏🏻❤️🏎
